I am especially grateful for life today, as it marks the 8th anniversary of my bike accident on March 7, 2015. That day changed my life forever, but it also taught me valuable lessons about resilience, gratitude, and the power of the human spirit to overcome adversity.

Reflecting on the blessing of life and the opportunity to grow through challenges fills my heart ❤️ It also reminds me to appreciate every moment and live each day with purpose. Life is fragile and fleeting, but it is also a precious gift.

I am thankful for the struggles I’ve faced, for they have shaped me into the person I am today. Here’s your reminder to embrace each day with gratitude and a steadfast determination to live your best life. 

Move your body, love your people and never ever give up. ✌🏼

Let’s keep living ❤️🙏🏼

#gratitude #mementomori #growthmindset #liveeachday #blessed #accidentanniversary #resilience #overcomingadversity

We’ve committed to 1 life-additive adventure or challenge per month for the next 30 years, we ticked a few things off the list on this trip ✌🏼 

More to come @the375life

A week in Mexico 🇲🇽 with @elizabeth_rose_3_3 & @travmckenzie 

When we started this journey to document our love of adventure, we determined that one trip/adventure/challenge per month for 30 years was 375 incredible experiences. While we have the time, energy and resources to see this beautiful world we’re going to do it! 

What are the things you’ve been holding off on doing the we can help you achieve? 

Here’s what we ticked off our list in 1 week 
#28 - take TJM to his first all-inclusive resort 
#78 - swim in a Cenote 
#79 - take a pottery class together 
#80 - ride an ATV in the jungle
